    <div class="comment-text editable-message-text" itemprop="commentText"><p>Empathy stores your authentication information into your private keyring that is only accessible by you with the password you use to unlock it. There is no &quot;public keyring&quot;. Pidgin stores your account passwords in clear text in a file with appropriate user permissions.</p></div>
    
    
    
